The paper deals with computing singular values of a large sparse matrix in a distributed setting using the MapReduce framework. This involves techniques from distributed computing, linear algebra, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper also discusses methods for preserving singular values with relative error, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses techniques for reducing shuffle size and complexity, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
